from heke heikki paananen subject re how do di box work in article lancer stephe lewi foskett write i do sound for a couple of band around here and we need direct input box for the keyboard these be the little box that take a line level out of the keyboard and transform it into low-z for the run to the mixer sadly they cost like or more each and i go to need like or of them i look inside one belong to another band and it look like just a transformer do anyone have any plan for build them perhap in anderton electronic project for musician book which i be have a hell of a time track down an easy way to solve the problem be to use two op-amp to form the balance low-z output but thi solution do not provide any galvanic isolation between keyboard or whatever plug and mixer if no tight requiremet be demand and some hum snap crackle and pop sound form by grind loop can be tolerate the op-amp solution be just what you be look for it be cheap somewhat not sure but craig anderton do introduce one di-box project in guitar player mag year ago transformerles thank a lot hope thi help email if more detail want lancer modimidofrsaso mein kopf ist ein labyrinth mein leben ist ein minenfeld heikki paananen heke the university of oulu department of electrical engineer just a student finland home be where the heart ly but if the heart ly where be home fish 